First Lady Melania Trump delivered remarks at the International Women of Courage Award ceremony, honoring women who have shown courage and leadership in advocating for peace, justice, human rights, equality, and women's empowerment. She emphasized the importance of courage and how it sets apart those who believe in a higher calling and act on it. Melania Trump highlighted the stories of courageous women who have survived brutal attacks, served in the military, and fought against human trafficking. She expressed gratitude to the State Department and American diplomats for their work in pursuing a more free and prosperous world. Melania Trump concluded her remarks by thanking the honorees for being role models and wishing blessings upon them and the United States of America.